A student passes the course when she/he:
- has attended at least 50% of the lectures;
- has participated in the last seminar;
- has received at least 50 points in total for the assignments (2 homeworks and 1 online test), including at least 15 points for each separate assignment.

A student can receive up to 10 extra points for active participation in the lectures and seminars. These points are awarded at the discretion of the lecturers.

In case a student needs a grade for the course (in particular, foreign students), the grade will be determined in the following manner:
A = 91-100 points;
B = 81-90 points;
C = 71-80 points;
D = 61-70 points;
E = 51-60 points;
F = below 50 points.

