hindmaismeetod:
The course is evaluated on a pass/fail basis. To pass the course, the participants must:
1)	Attend 7 meetings out of 8 (exceptions granted in well-founded cases, if instructor is informed about absence in advance). NOTE: this is an in-person course but it will be possible to join online if you request this option at least 24 hours in advance.
2)	PhD student's period plan submitted and approved;
3)	submit a short (max 1.5 pages) statement that identifies three journals to which you could submit your research and justifies your choices;
4)	submit a 250-word 'web page profile' that introduces you as a PhD student and your dissertation project, along with your ORCID ID, a link to your completed ETIS profile, and a link to your profile on one international academic networking site of your choice  (e.g. Google scholar, ResearchGate, academia.edu, etc);
5)	submit a conference paper abstract (250 words), along with a justification (about half a page) for why you want to attend the conference in question, as well as an indicative budget for the conference trip;  
6)	submit a 1-page reflection on ethics issues and considerations pertaining to your research;
7)	submit a 1-page rationale section of an imaginary research funding proposal, providing reasons for why your research should be funded, considering both academic and societal relevance.

