hindmaismeetod:
The final grade is composed of the results of the discussion paper (40%) and the poster/poster presentation (60%).

1. The discussion paper provides an opportunity to explore and analyze a selected global governance arrangement in greater detail. 

The discussion paper is assessed according to:
-	the precision of the description and explanation of defining features of the governance arrangement through the prism of relevant concepts;
-	sufficiency of empirical evidence and explanations for the findings regarding the effectiveness or legitimacy of the governance arrangement;
-	contextualization of findings with a view on other governance arrangements and wider debates in the study of global governance;
-	sufficiency of relevant conceptual and empirical sources;
-	adherence to the formatting requirements.

2. The poster assignment is a collaborative assignment and is prepared in small groups. On the poster, course participants present findings from their analysis of a specific global governance arrangement.

The poster and the poster presentation are assessed according to:
-	description of the governance arrangement and its defining features by applying relevant conceptual categories;
-	the sufficiency of relevant empirical information to support the assessment of the effectiveness and legitimacy of the governance arrangement;
-	contextualization of the governance arrangement in relation to other relevant governance arrangements and wider debates in the study of global governance;
-	the effective use of visualizations for presenting information and adherence to the formatting requirements of an academic poster;
-	the effectiveness of the oral presentation of the poster.

